    "caption": "Sleeping twenty-two hours a day in a eucalyptus tree — and perfectly content.",
    "shortDescription": "Koalas sleep almost the entire day because eucalyptus leaves are tough, fibrous, mildly toxic, and nearly impossible to digest — it takes that much rest just to recover from a meal. They have two thumbs on each front paw for gripping branches, and they almost never come down to the ground. Fun fact: A koala's fingerprints are so close to human fingerprints that even forensic scientists have a hard time telling them apart under a microscope."
